Fortuitous discoveries of digestive tract tumors during the evaluation of hepatic tumors by lipiodol intra-arterial injection. Diagnostic application in a case of pancreatic tumor. The authors report three cases of extrahepatic lipiodol enhancement: two fortuitous discoveries of gastric and duodenal leiomyomas during the management of malignant hepatic lesion and a pancreatic surgical detection of an insulinoma which had not been detected with conventional techniques. The principles of the technique are described. The basis of its application to the pancreatic region is purposed and the future developments of pancreatic studies are discussed.